---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Scheduling"
  description="The full calendar of the practice in one view, self-scheduling for clients, a waitlist that doesn't slip, and clear at-a-glance status on every session."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Scheduling"
    title="The schedule, <em>without the spreadsheet.</em>"
    lede="A calendar that works for the practice admin managing four clinicians, the solo clinician who wants clients to self-book, and the supervisor who needs to see where the team is on any given afternoon."
  >
    <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Request access</a>
  </PageHeader>

  <section class="capabilities">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
        <h2>A calendar that maps to how a practice actually runs.</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Every clinician's calendar, in one view</h4>
          <p>Practice admins see the whole practice at once. Clinicians see their own. Supervisees can see their supervisor's openings when they're booking a joint session.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Availability your clinicians set</h4>
          <p>Each clinician sets the windows they're available. Clients can self-book against those windows from the portal. No back-and-forth about times. No phone tag.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Calendars stay in sync</h4>
          <p>Praxnote syncs with Google Calendar today. Your personal calendar and your practice availability stay separate — your spouse can't accidentally see a client's name, and a personal appointment doesn't show up to a client as "available."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>A waitlist that doesn't slip</h4>
          <p>See who's on the waitlist, what they're waiting for, and how long they've been waiting. Move clients from waiting to scheduled when an opening appears. Nothing dissolves into "I think someone emailed about that."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>The right rate on the right session</h4>
          <p>Each kind of session has a code and a default rate. If a clinician's license, contract, or experience calls for a different rate, override it for them. The right number applies every time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Status, at a glance</h4>
          <p>Scheduled, signed, no-show, late-cancel, clinician-cancelled — each has a clear icon on the calendar. You can see where the day stands without clicking into anything.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="self-sched alt">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">When the client books their own time</p>
        <h2>Clients book against openings. <em>Without a phone call.</em></h2>
        <p class="lede">
          From the portal: the client picks the kind of session, sees the openings on their clinician's
          calendar (or any clinician, if they're new), confirms. They're guided through it one step at
          a time so they always know what to do next.
        </p>
      </header>

      <ul class="checks">
        <li>The practice's cancellation policy is enforced quietly in the portal</li>
        <li>Reminder emails and texts go out on the cadence the practice has set</li>
        <li>Late-cancel and no-show fees flow into billing automatically, if your practice charges them</li>
        <li>Telehealth works through the providers Praxnote supports; native video is coming</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    eyebrow="See it on a real week"
    heading="Walk a Tuesday through the calendar."
    body="Bring a recent week — an availability change, a waitlist client to schedule, a session that needs to be marked no-show. We'll walk how each one plays out."
    primaryHref="/demo"
    primaryLabel="Book a walk-through"
    secondaryHref="/features/client-portal"
    secondaryLabel="See the client portal"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .capabilities { padding: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0; }
  .alt { background: var(--paper-warm); border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
  .self-sched { padding: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0; }
  .section-head { max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .section-head .lede { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .card h4 { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .card p { color: var(--stone-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.65; }
</style>
